Datasheet

Component: LM393 Comparator IC

The LM393 is a dual differential comparator designed to compare two input voltages and provide a digital output. It operates over a wide supply voltage range and is commonly used in voltage detection, monitoring circuits, and signal comparison applications.

Important Specifications

Supply Voltage Range: 2 V – 36 V

Input Offset Voltage: Typically 2 mV

Low Power Consumption

Open Collector Output

Dual Comparator in a single IC package

Operating Temperature Range: 0°C to 70°C (standard version)

Applications

Voltage threshold detection

Battery level indicator circuits

Signal comparison circuits

Power supply monitoring systems

Sensor signal conditioning

